Function example:
********************

val pi = 3.14;
fun area r = pi*r*r;


Comments begin with (* and end with *)


An alphabetic name must
• begin with a letter
• followed by any number of letters, digits, underscores, or primes (')

Avoid ML keyboards:
• abstype, and, andalso, as, case, datatype, do, else, end, eqtype, exception, fn, fun, functor, handle, if, in, include, infix, infixr, let, nonfix, of, op, open, orelse, raise, rec, charing, sig, signature, sturct, structure, then, type, val, where, while, with, withtype

Minus sign = ~

Integer operations:
addition (+) , subtraction (-) , multiplcation (*) , division (div), remainder (mod)

Real numbers --> contain a decimal point or E notation (0.01, ~1.2E12)

Infix operators for reals include (+, -, *, and /)


To specify type of the argument
********************************
fun square(x : real) = x*x;  (can omit the parentheses)


Arithmetic and the standard library -> abs, min, max, sign
************************************

Int.abs ~4;
> 4 : int
Int.min(7, Int.sign 12);
> 1 : int

Converting int to real -> real(i) which converts i to the equivalent real number

Calling real(i) --> converts i to the equivalent real number

Calling round(r) --> converts r to the nearest integer


Other real-to-integer conversions --> floor, ceil, trunc

Structure Math on real numbers --> sqrt, sin, cos, atan(inverse tan), exp and In(natural logarithm)

Concatenation operator --> (^)

Function size (it) --> returns the number of chars in a string


Special Characters:

\n --> inserts a newline
\t --> inserts a tabulation
\" --> inserts a double quote
\\ --> inserts a backlash
\ followed by a newline and other white-space characters, followed by another \ inserts nothing but continues a string across the line break
